<div class="textbox">
    <div class="popuptitle">ChocolateChip Cookies</div>
   Simple and Easy Recipe for Everyone.<br /> <br />Click on a marker to learn more about each ingredient.
</div>


<p> <span>PREHEAT</span> over to 375 degrees (F).<br /> <br /><span>COMBINE</span> flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl. Beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract in large mixer bowl until creamy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels.  Add nuts for additional flavor if desired. Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheets. <br /><br /><span>BAKE</span> for 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on baking sheets for 2 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool completely. </p>
<img src="http://wannacomewith.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/chocolate-chip-cookies-9980.jpg" alt= "drugs"/>

